@page "/privacy";
@model PrivacyModel
@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Privacy Policy";
}

<div class="privacy-container">
    <h1>@ViewData["Title"]</h1>

    <p>
        Effective Date: 01/30/2024
        Last Updated: 11/30/2024
        [Your Website Name] ("we," "our," or "us") values your privacy 
        and is committed to protecting your personal information. 
        This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, store, 
        and protect data managed on our platform, which is designed 
        for administrative purposes using a CRUD (Create, Read, Update, Delete) 
        data management system.
    </p>

    <h2>1. Information We Collect</h2>
    <p>We may collect and process the following types of information:</p>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Personal Information:</strong> Names, email addresses, phone numbers, or other contact details provided during user registration or account setup.</li>
        <li><strong>Administrative Data:</strong> Data created, updated, or managed by users in the CRUD system.</li>
        <li><strong>Technical Data:</strong> IP addresses, browser types, operating systems, and other system information collected during your use of the platform.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>2. How We Use Your Information</h2>
    <p>Your data is processed for the following purposes:</p>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Operational Needs:</strong> Managing and maintaining data entered into the CRUD system.</li>
        <li><strong>Authentication and Security:</strong> Ensuring authorized access to the platform and preventing unauthorized activities.</li>
        <li><strong>Improvement and Development:</strong> Enhancing the platform's functionality, troubleshooting, and implementing updates.</li>
        <li><strong>Compliance:</strong> Adhering to legal, regulatory, and contractual obligations.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>3. Data Sharing and Disclosure</h2>
    <p>We do not sell or rent your personal information. However, we may share information:</p>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>With Service Providers:</strong> Third-party providers that assist with hosting, security, or data management services.</li>
        <li><strong>For Legal Obligations:</strong> When required by law, such as responding to lawful requests by public authorities or complying with legal processes.</li>
        <li><strong>In Business Transactions:</strong> If part of the platform is transferred or merged with another entity, your data may be transferred as part of that process.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>4. Data Storage and Retention</h2>
    <p>Your data is securely stored using industry-standard security measures. Data managed through the CRUD system will be retained for as long as necessary to fulfill the purposes outlined in this policy or comply with legal obligations.</p>

    <h2>5. Your Rights</h2>
    <p>You have the following rights regarding your data:</p>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Access and Correction:</strong> Review, update, or delete personal data associated with your account.</li>
        <li><strong>Data Portability:</strong> Request a copy of your data in a structured format.</li>
        <li><strong>Right to Erasure:</strong> Request the deletion of your data, subject to legal and operational constraints.</li>
        <li><strong>Object or Restrict Processing:</strong> Limit how your data is used in certain circumstances.</li>
    </ul>
    <p>To exercise your rights, please contact us at [Insert Contact Information].</p>

    <h2>6. Security Measures</h2>
    <p>We implement measures such as encryption, access controls, and regular audits to protect your data. While we strive to ensure data security, no system can guarantee 100% protection.</p>

    <h2>7. Cookies and Tracking Technologies</h2>
    <p>Our platform may use cookies and similar technologies to enhance functionality and analyze usage. You can manage cookie preferences through your browser settings.</p>

    <h2>8. Third-Party Links</h2>
    <p>Our website may include links to third-party sites. We are not responsible for the privacy practices of these external platforms.</p>

    <h2>9. Updates to this Policy</h2>
    <p>We may update this Privacy Policy to reflect changes in our practices or for other operational, legal, or regulatory reasons. The updated policy will be posted with a revised effective date.</p>

    <h2>10. Contact Us</h2>
    <p>If you have questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy, please contact us:</p>
    <div class="contact-info">
        <p><strong>Email:</strong> mconocimiento123@gmail.com<br>
        <strong>Phone:</strong> 677 2891 232 <br>
    </div>

    <p>By using our platform, you agree to this Privacy Policy. If you do not agree, please refrain from using the system.</p>
</div>